    "Though effective, the SMILES-VAEs suffer from the same issue that plagues most seq2seq models (namely, the inability to produce 100% verified SMILES strings).",
    "Research groups have shown (Li et al., 2018b; Liu et al., 2018; Samanta et al., 2020; Jin et al., 2023a; Jin et al., 2023b; Jin et al., 2023c), that molecular generators based on molecular graphs can solve the 100% verified SMILES challenge.",
    "One such conditional graph generator for multi-objective de novo (i) Some GAI models; (ii) De novo molecular design workflow (involving transfer learning to address data scarcity) for generating small molecules against a pre-decided target.",
    "(A) Pre-trained deep generative model.",
    "(B) TL to learn the essential characteristics of small compounds concerning the target receptor, and RL approach to enhance the molecular properties in the desired direction."
